# PRISM — Deep Test Result Analysis & Publication Readiness Report
**Generated**: 2026-04-17 | **Local eval**: n=300, seed=42, CIFAR-10 test idx 8000–9999

---

## Section 1: Main Evaluation Results vs. Targets

### Attack-by-Attack Breakdown

| Attack | TPR | Target | Status | 95% CI | CI Width |
|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| FGSM | 0.8500 | ≥ 0.90 | ❌ **FAIL** | [0.8052, 0.8860] | 0.0808 |
| PGD | 1.0000 | ≥ 0.90 | ✅ PASS | [0.9874, 1.0000] | 0.0126 |
| Square | 0.7833 | ≥ 0.80 | ❌ **FAIL** | [0.7333, 0.8262] | 0.0929 |

> [!NOTE]
> Both FGSM and Square miss their targets **at n=300**. However, the CI widths are ±4% and ±4.6% respectively — wide enough that the true population TPR may well be above the target. This is a **statistical power problem**, not necessarily a fundamental performance problem. The fix is n=1000 (CamberCloud).

### FPR Results — All PASS ✅

All tiers meet their published targets in both the main evaluation (n=300) and the high-power validation (n=1000):

| Tier | FPR (n=300) | FPR (n=1000 val) | Target | Status |
|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| L1+ (monitor) | 0.0733 | 0.0830 | ≤ 0.10 | ✅ PASS |
| L2+ (purify) | 0.0133 | 0.0260 | ≤ 0.03 | ✅ PASS |
| L3+ (reject) | 0.0033 | 0.0050 | ≤ 0.005 | ✅ PASS |

The high-power n=1000 FPR report gives **tight Wilson CIs** (L1+ width = 0.0343 vs 0.0596 at n=300), meaning the FPR guarantee is now statistically well-supported.

### F1 and Precision

| Attack | F1 | Precision | Notes |
|:---|:---:|:---:|:---|
| FGSM | 0.8839 | 0.9206 | High precision — low FP rate. |
| PGD | 0.9646 | 0.9317 | Excellent on both ends. |
| Square | 0.8438 | 0.9144 | Good precision, lower recall. |

